 ** This a memory resident program which implements comprehensive english **
 ** -russian dictionary (based on Fowler H.W. & Fowler F.G. " The concise **
 ** Oxford English Dictionary ").                                         **
 ** To execute GLOSSARY type :                                            **
 **          GLOSSARY [/R] [/DriveLetter:\GlossaryBasePath...]            **
 ** If GLOSSARY run without any options, the program executes a DOS SHELL **
 ** and can be removed from memory by typing EXIT at any DOS prompt.      **
 ** If GLOSSARY run with the /R option, the program is made resident.     **
 ** Once installed, it can be activated from within your program editor,  **
 ** debugger, programming environment, or at the DOS prompt.              **
 ** If GlossaryBasePath is omited, GLOSSARY will looks for base files     **
 ** in current directory.                                                 **
 ** If you want unload GLOSSARY from memory run it with /U option.        **
 ** Use /H option to display GLOSSARY help screen.                        **
 ** GLOSSARY uses about 4300 bytes of memory with /R option and 4900      **
 ** bytes without.                                                        **
 ** The hot key is ALT-G.                                                 **
 ***************************************************************************

